{
  "texts": [
    "Through reflective exercises and thought experiments, participants gain awareness about their preferences and values in relation to a specific system.",
    "The toolkit contains different tools such as worksheets and cards that facilitate the discussion and explicit statement of the participants' preferences regarding a system, used data types, essential values, and its application context.",
    "These exercises help in surfacing the concrete meaning of the abstract RAI concepts for the affected stakeholders.",
    "Especially the 'Participant Value Perception Sheet' on which participants can group the cards under different clusters such as 'opportunities', 'costs', or 'motivations' make these very explicit.",
    "The gained insights should inform the translation of the abstract RAI principles to the specific use case to ensure that the preferences of affected communities are reflected."
  ]
}